        <body>
             <div type="edition" subtype="ogham" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam" resp="#NW">             
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up-top-down"/><persName><name nymRef="#moddagnas"><supplied reason="undefined" evidence="previouseditor">ᚋᚑᚇᚇᚐᚌᚅ</supplied><supplied reason="lost">ᚔ</supplied></name> <w type="formula" lemma="maqqas">ᚋᚐᚊᚔ</w> <name nymRef="#gattagnas">ᚌᚐᚈ<supplied reason="lost">ᚈ</supplied>ᚐᚌᚅ<supplied reason="lost">ᚔ</supplied></name> <w type="formula" lemma="muccoviias">ᚋ<unclear reason="faded">ᚒ</unclear>ᚉᚑᚔ</w> <name nymRef="#lugunias?">ᚂᚒᚌ<supplied reason="undefined" evidence="previouseditor">ᚒᚅᚔ</supplied></name></persName>
                </ab> 
            </div>                    
            <div type="edition" subtype="transliteration" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam" xml:space="preserve" resp="#NW">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up-top-down"/><persName><name nymRef="#moddagnas"><supplied reason="undefined" evidence="previouseditor"> MODDAGN</supplied><supplied reason="lost">I</supplied></name> <w type="formula" lemma="maqqas">MAQI</w> <name nymRef="#gattagnas">GAT<supplied reason="lost">T</supplied>AGN<supplied reason="lost">I</supplied></name> <w type="formula" lemma="muccoviias">M<unclear reason="faded">U</unclear>COI</w> <name nymRef="#lugunias?">LUG<supplied reason="undefined" evidence="previouseditor">UNI</supplied></name></persName>
                </ab>
               <!-- <ab type="list"></ab>-->
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                <app n="1">   
                    <note>The inscribed stone isn't fully accessible in situ and the first name (MODDAGN[I]) and some of the last (-UNI), read by Macalister (1945, 295) are beneath ground level. A viable alternative to GAT[T]AGN[I] is, as Brash (1879, 268) read:</note> <rdg>GATIGNI</rdg> 
                </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p>of Múadán son of Gáethíne(?) descendant of Luigne(?)</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <!-- <p>The inscription contains the formula words MAQI and MUCOI. MAQI is related to <distinct xml:lang="sga"><ref target="https://dil.ie/31166">mac, macc</ref></distinct> 'son', and MUCOI is possibly related to <distinct xml:lang="sga"><ref target="https://dil.ie/31187">maccu, moccu</ref></distinct> 'belonging to the family of' (Stifter 2025). </p>-->
            </div>
